node.text:
Here’s how we use our Letter templates to add monograms to our charcuterie boards.
-
We attach our Letter Template to the board using @akfixna 705 and painters tape. Then we use a router with a @toolstoday 47222-S bit to pocket out the letter. 
Then we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast with @beaverdustpigments to fill the void. After it cures, a quick sand using @sia_abrasives_jjscanada sanding starting at 80 grit and finishing at 220 grit.
Last, we use some @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil to finish the board.
These acrylic templates are a great way to customize charcuterie boards for beginners and pros.
-
Shop wood, epoxy, templates, pigments and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com
-
#Acrylic #Epoxy #Template #Resin #WoodWorking #Custom #Charcuterie

node.title: How To Add A Monogram To A Charcuterie Board!

node.text:
Our FIRST @beaverdustpigments Product is NOW AVAILABLE for purchase! Only 50 are available.
-
It’s a Variety Pack #1. It includes 5 grams of 20 different colours. This one is specifically focused on cool tones so it’s full of greens and blues.
-
You can order this Variety Pack now at www.JeffMackSupply.com. You can also browse the colours we will have in stock soon and you can even sign up to be notified when the rest of the products are in stock via a “sold out” product page!
-
#BeaverDust #BeaverDustPigments #MicaPowder #Pigment #Epoxy #Resin

node.text:
Looking for an easy DIY Project!?
-
We now have these letter templates available so you can create your own custom monogram boards!
-
This video shows the steps we take to create a piece like this.
-
Here’s what we used:
Here's What We Used:
WOOD: Roasted Maple (from our 4"-8" wide listing)
EPOXY: @squidpoxy Clear Fast (perfect for small pours like this)
PIGMENT: @blackdiamondpigments_com "White Diamond Effect"
TEMPLATES: 1/4" Large Round and the Letter "S" (we have the whole alphabet available now)
TAPE: Painters Tape
TEMPLATE ADHESIVE: @akfixna 705 Universal Max Adhesive
ROUTER BIT: 3/16" flush trim router bit from @toolstoday 
FINISH: @rubiomonocoatusa Pure 2C Oil
-
Shop all these supplies and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com
FREE SHIPPING to Canada and USA on orders over $235USD ($300CAD)
-

node.text:
Here’s how we use our Letter templates to add monograms to our charcuterie boards.
-
We attach our Letter Template to the board using @akfixna 705 and painters tape. Then we use a router with a @toolstoday 47222-S bit to pocket out the letter. 
Then we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast with @beaverdustpigments to fill the void. After it cures, a quick sand using @sia_abrasives_jjscanada sanding starting at 80 grit and finishing at 220 grit.
Last, we use some @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil to finish the board.
These acrylic templates are a great way to customize charcuterie boards for beginners and pros.
-
Shop wood, epoxy, templates, pigments and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com
-
#Acrylic #Epoxy #Template #Resin #WoodWorking #Custom #Charcuterie

@empire.molds 
COMING SOON!
-
Go hit that follow button and be the first to know when we launch our brand new Mold company!
-
This has been in the works for a while, designing and testing and we are almost ready to launch! 🚀 
-
These forms are designed using one piece of HDPE with a built in flange that allows for easy clamping. These are thermal formed so there’s no welds which means no cracking or breaking!
-
Let us know if you have any questions!
-
#Maker #HDPE #NoSealForm #Resin #Epoxy #Reusable #NoCracking #Craft
